ce:section.ce:para:
The corrosion resistance performances of blank plate (Ti), MXene coating (Ti-MXene) and MXene/NCDs coating (Ti-MXene/NCDs) in SBF solution were tested by electrochemical analyzer (Gamry, Reference 3000 electrochemical workstation, USA). The prepared sample was tested with three electrode electrochemical method, the working electrode was the prepared plate, the opposite electrode and the reference electrode was platinum electrode and calomel electrode respectively. Moreover, the obtained data were analyzed by Origin software, and fitted the corrosion current density (I

                           corr
                        ) data and corrosion potential (E

                           corr
                        ) curve. Repeat the test at least 3 times for each sample to avoid errors.

Due to the visualized comparison of the different coatings, the three-dimensional (3D) profile of wear scars, the wear volume, the thickness and the roughness (R

                           a
                        ) of Ti-MXene/NCDs and Ti-Mxene samples were observed and calculate by white light interferometer (WLI, Bruker, Contour GT-K0). The chemical compositions of MXene and MXene/NCDs coatings were analyzed by X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy (XPS, AXIS UltraDLD, Kratos, Japan), and equipped with a microfocused, monochromatic Al Kɑ X-ray (hυ = 1500 eV) source.

Moreover, the adhesion ability effected the surface passivates the contact and significantly reduced the interface adhesion. As shown in Fig. 8(b2 - b4) and Fig. 10(b2 - b4), abrasive wear and adhesive wear can be observed in the EDX and SEM image. This result from the uneven dispersion of MXene lamella and the insufficient hydrogen bond between MXene and dopamine (DA). In our study, as shown in the schematic diagram for biotribological mechanisms (Fig. 12
                        ). Considering the sliding of carbon quantum dots between layers can extend the layer spacing of MXene and give full play to the interlayer shear mechanism [77]. Additionally, the addition of carbon quantum dots, as observed in Fig. 4(c), leads to a more uniform dispersion of MXene. In our work, there are extensive chemical bonding forces and a large number of van der Waals forces (hydrogen bonding) between nitrogen-doped carbon quantum dots (NCDs), DA and MXene, resulting in stronger mechanical properties of the coating. Such as, the carboxyl groups from the surface of NCDs respectively reacted with the amino groups from DA and the hydroxyl group of MXene. Moreover, the amino groups and the carboxyl groups from NCDs, the amino groups on DA as well as the hydroxyl group of MXene constituted the hydrogen-bond network. Furthermore, it can be seen that NCD presented smaller spherical in Fig. 4(a) SEM image. MXene dispersed more evenly with the addition of NCDs. The roughness (R

                           a
                        ) of Ti-MXene/NCDs sample obtained by 3D white light interferometer is 3.82 μm, the Ti-MXene is 5.589 μm. The calculated elastic modulus (E), maximum contact pressure (Pmax) and maximum shear stress (τmax) of Ti, Ti-MXene and Ti-MXene/NCDs were listed in the following Table 4.

The calculated maximum Hertz contact pressure (
P max
) and the maximum shear stress (τmax) of Ti-MXene and Ti-MXene have been reduced to varying degrees. This was consistent with the analysis of tribological performance. The calculated lubrication film thickness (
h min
) is 1.26 μm, and the λ value is 0.33, implying the fluid lubrication statement. Due to the slipping effect between MXene sheets [75] and the rolling effect of carbon quantum dots in the friction process led to the “dual-action” effect, sliding friction and rolling friction. At the same time, the intercalation structure of MXene/NCDs and the chemical and hydrogen bonds all served as the stable protective film during the friction process of SBF solution, hindering the direct contact between the friction pairs, reducing the friction coefficient and wear [78]. Therefore, the excellent tribological performance of MXene/NCDs related to its own physical properties, also depended on the chemical reactions that occur during friction.
